WEBVTT

00:00:07.214 --> 00:00:10.454
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:00:10.487 --> 00:00:17.669
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:00:24.048 --> 00:00:25.483
- [grunts]

00:00:29.592 --> 00:00:33.266
<i>[soft music]</i>

00:00:34.603 --> 00:00:35.638
[gasps]

00:00:35.671 --> 00:00:37.809
- What could that possibly be?

00:00:37.842 --> 00:00:39.179
It's a sword.

00:00:39.212 --> 00:00:41.817
But it's gotta be
at least 300 years old.

00:00:41.850 --> 00:00:44.288
- I think you're right! It is!

00:00:44.321 --> 00:00:46.827
This is crazy!
What should we do?

00:00:46.860 --> 00:00:48.731
[both panting]

00:00:48.765 --> 00:00:51.603
[Kotetsu] Is your heart about
to beat out of your chest too?

00:00:51.637 --> 00:00:53.407
- Yeah!
- Mr. Tanjiro,

00:00:53.440 --> 00:00:55.978
you came here because you
need a new sword, right?

00:00:56.012 --> 00:00:57.148
If that's the case,

00:00:57.181 --> 00:00:59.185
then it only makes sense
you take this one!

00:00:59.218 --> 00:01:01.623
- No, no, no, no, no!
That wouldn't be right!

00:01:01.657 --> 00:01:04.061
- The steel they used
in the Sengoku period

00:01:04.094 --> 00:01:05.331
is the best quality ever!

00:01:05.364 --> 00:01:07.134
- No, no, I couldn't!

00:01:07.168 --> 00:01:08.738
- But the only reason
we found it

00:01:08.771 --> 00:01:10.073
is 'cause you broke it!

00:01:10.106 --> 00:01:12.679
- That's just because
it took damage for 300 years!

00:01:12.713 --> 00:01:15.050
And I just so happened
to be there training with it

00:01:15.083 --> 00:01:16.219
when it finally broke!

00:01:16.252 --> 00:01:18.624
- Are you sure
you don't want it?

00:01:18.657 --> 00:01:20.629
- [moans]

00:01:20.662 --> 00:01:23.467
- How about we pull it out
just to take a look?

00:01:23.501 --> 00:01:25.839
- I thought you'd never ask!
Let's do it!

00:01:25.872 --> 00:01:28.610
[both laugh nervously]

00:01:31.817 --> 00:01:33.486
- It's rusty.

00:01:33.520 --> 00:01:36.927
- Oh, yeah.
I guess that makes sense, huh?

00:01:36.960 --> 00:01:40.668
It has been neglected for
the last 300 years, hasn't it?

00:01:40.701 --> 00:01:43.607
Sorry I got us
both worked up for nothing.

00:01:44.609 --> 00:01:45.711
- That's okay!

00:01:45.745 --> 00:01:47.281
I don't mind at all!

00:01:47.314 --> 00:01:50.153
- Whoa! Please don't cry,
Mr. Tanjiro!

00:01:50.187 --> 00:01:51.557
I'm sorry!

00:01:51.590 --> 00:01:52.559
[heavy thud]

00:01:52.592 --> 00:01:53.927
[both gasp]

00:01:53.961 --> 00:01:55.364
- What's that?
- [heavy thud]

00:01:55.397 --> 00:01:58.604
<i>[chorus vocalizing]</i>

00:02:01.510 --> 00:02:02.545
[gasps]

00:02:03.881 --> 00:02:05.885
<i>["Kizuna no Kiseki" playing]</i>

00:02:05.918 --> 00:02:12.932
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:03:35.865 --> 00:03:38.871
<i>[singers vocalizing]</i>

00:03:42.277 --> 00:03:43.247
[heavy thud]

00:03:43.280 --> 00:03:45.083
<i>[traditional music]</i>

00:03:45.117 --> 00:03:46.253
- [grunts]

00:03:46.286 --> 00:03:48.056
- [wails] Who's that?

00:03:48.089 --> 00:03:49.325
Mr. Haganezuka?!

00:03:49.358 --> 00:03:52.464
- No need to explain.
I heard everything.

00:03:52.497 --> 00:03:54.636
Allow me to take it from here.

00:03:54.670 --> 00:03:56.206
[Kotetsu]
Take what from here?

00:03:56.239 --> 00:03:58.977
- [grunting]

00:03:59.011 --> 00:04:00.314
- What do you think
you're doing?

00:04:00.347 --> 00:04:02.519
- Just leave it to me!

00:04:02.552 --> 00:04:03.921
- Please, let go of it!

00:04:03.954 --> 00:04:06.326
And why are you trying
to take off with it, anyway?!

00:04:06.359 --> 00:04:08.797
- Quit asking questions,
and leave it to me!

00:04:08.831 --> 00:04:10.568
- You can't just show up
out of the blue

00:04:10.601 --> 00:04:12.939
and say, "Leave it to me!"
That doesn't make sense!

00:04:12.973 --> 00:04:14.743
- You just leave it to me!

00:04:14.777 --> 00:04:17.348
- Not a chance!
This belongs to Kotetsu!

00:04:17.381 --> 00:04:19.318
- Just leave it to me!

00:04:19.351 --> 00:04:22.158
- You know, I came
all the way here to see you!

00:04:22.191 --> 00:04:23.561
Where have you been hiding?!

00:04:23.594 --> 00:04:26.366
- [gasps]

00:04:26.399 --> 00:04:29.138
"Leave it to me"
means leave it to me!

00:04:29.172 --> 00:04:30.842
- I asked you
what you meant by that,

00:04:30.875 --> 00:04:33.547
'cause we have no idea what
the heck you're talking about!

00:04:33.581 --> 00:04:36.921
- What part of "Leave it to me"
don't you two understand?

00:04:36.954 --> 00:04:38.156
[both yelp]

00:04:38.190 --> 00:04:41.462
- What kind of grown-up
acts like that?!

00:04:42.264 --> 00:04:43.534
- Pay attention, boys.

00:04:43.567 --> 00:04:46.372
Mr. Haganezuka's weak spots
are his sides.

00:04:46.405 --> 00:04:47.843
All you gotta do is this.

00:04:47.876 --> 00:04:49.980
- Tickle, tickle, tickle...
- [laughing]

00:04:50.013 --> 00:04:50.948
- Tickle, tickle, tickle...

00:04:50.981 --> 00:04:53.252
- Hey, Mr. Kanamori!
- [laughter continues]

00:04:53.286 --> 00:04:54.421
- Long time no see.

00:04:54.455 --> 00:04:57.494
- Hey, long time
no see, Tanjiro.

00:04:57.528 --> 00:04:59.599
- Mr. Haganezuka
always goes limp for a while

00:04:59.632 --> 00:05:03.440
after being tickled, so I'll
do the explaining for him.

00:05:04.375 --> 00:05:06.814
Please try your best
to forgive Mr. Haganezuka.

00:05:06.847 --> 00:05:10.922
You see, he's been hiding out
in the mountains, training.

00:05:10.955 --> 00:05:12.191
- Training?

00:05:12.224 --> 00:05:15.832
- That's right. All in order
to forge you a stronger sword

00:05:15.865 --> 00:05:17.969
so that you won't
be killed in battle.

00:05:18.002 --> 00:05:19.606
- Ahh.

00:05:19.640 --> 00:05:22.044
- But he'd never
admit that himself.

00:05:22.077 --> 00:05:24.849
- He did that for me?

00:05:24.883 --> 00:05:28.123
- All this time, you've been
asking Mr. Haganezuka

00:05:28.156 --> 00:05:29.593
for another sword, right?

00:05:29.626 --> 00:05:31.663
I'm sure it made him very happy.

00:05:31.697 --> 00:05:34.368
After all,
he's always losing clients,

00:05:34.401 --> 00:05:36.205
because most swordsmen
can't stand him.

00:05:36.238 --> 00:05:37.709
- I never would have guessed.

00:05:37.743 --> 00:05:41.315
- This guy's got about the worst
social skills I've ever seen.

00:05:41.348 --> 00:05:42.384
- Huh?
- It's no wonder

00:05:42.418 --> 00:05:44.121
he still can't
find himself a bride.

00:05:44.155 --> 00:05:45.157
- [moans]
- [gasps]

00:05:45.190 --> 00:05:46.994
- Oh, look. He's been revived.

00:05:47.027 --> 00:05:50.735
- I shall take this ancient,
rusty sword into my care.

00:05:50.768 --> 00:05:53.473
And by using
the Nichirin Sword polishing art

00:05:53.507 --> 00:05:55.277
of the Haganezuka family,

00:05:55.310 --> 00:05:57.682
I will surely be able
to restore it!

00:05:57.715 --> 00:05:59.485
- Why didn't you
just say all that

00:05:59.519 --> 00:06:01.389
from the start, you big dummy,

00:06:01.423 --> 00:06:03.159
instead of repeating,
"Leave it to me,"

00:06:03.192 --> 00:06:04.495
like some kind of maniac?

00:06:04.530 --> 00:06:06.667
Well, guess that's
expecting too much.

00:06:06.700 --> 00:06:09.104
- What the hell just
came out of your mouth?!

00:06:09.137 --> 00:06:10.875
I dare you to say that again!

00:06:10.908 --> 00:06:12.444
- Ulp! I can't breathe!

00:06:12.477 --> 00:06:14.550
- [Tanjiro] Whoa, whoa...
- His sides! His sides!

00:06:14.583 --> 00:06:16.319
Quick, go for his sides!

00:06:16.352 --> 00:06:18.056
- Tickle, tickle, tickle...
- [laughing]

00:06:18.089 --> 00:06:20.260
- Tickle, tickle, tickle!
Tickle, tickle, tickle!

00:06:20.293 --> 00:06:22.264
- [panting]

00:06:22.297 --> 00:06:25.436
<i>[playful music]</i>

00:06:26.774 --> 00:06:29.478
- I'll be taking
this sword with me.

00:06:29.513 --> 00:06:31.951
This one should hold you over
while I work on it.

00:06:31.984 --> 00:06:33.654
<i>[sentimental music]</i>

00:06:33.687 --> 00:06:36.125
- [gasps]

00:06:37.361 --> 00:06:38.330
Oh.

00:06:38.363 --> 00:06:40.968
Th--Thank you very much!

00:06:42.004 --> 00:06:44.542
So, yeah, that's what
happened yesterday, see.

00:06:44.576 --> 00:06:46.479
They say it takes
three days and three nights

00:06:46.513 --> 00:06:47.815
to properly polish a sword,

00:06:47.849 --> 00:06:51.155
so he'll be finished
the day after tomorrow.

00:06:51.189 --> 00:06:52.424
I'm worried, though.

00:06:52.457 --> 00:06:54.729
They say that polishing art
of his is so brutal

00:06:54.762 --> 00:06:56.432
that some have died doing it.

00:06:56.465 --> 00:06:58.671
- [shuddering]
- I know he strictly forbade me

00:06:58.704 --> 00:07:01.843
from checking in on him,
but maybe I should, right?

00:07:01.876 --> 00:07:04.081
- I don't know!
And I don't care!

00:07:04.114 --> 00:07:06.586
Now stop talking to me
like we're friends or something!

00:07:06.620 --> 00:07:09.392
- Huh? Hold on,
you mean we're not friends?

00:07:09.425 --> 00:07:10.962
- Not by a long shot, idiot!

00:07:10.995 --> 00:07:13.567
Do I have to remind you
that you broke my arm?

00:07:13.601 --> 00:07:15.538
Don't tell me
you've already forgotten!

00:07:15.571 --> 00:07:16.773
[bone cracks]

00:07:18.510 --> 00:07:20.079
- I remember
it being your own fault

00:07:20.113 --> 00:07:22.819
because you hit a girl, Genya.
I had no choice.

00:07:22.852 --> 00:07:25.123
- Don't ever call me
by my first name!

00:07:25.156 --> 00:07:27.562
- These rice crackers are tasty!

00:07:27.595 --> 00:07:29.331
- Want one?
- Damn you!

00:07:29.365 --> 00:07:32.037
No, I don't want one! Get lost!

00:07:33.073 --> 00:07:34.642
- Wait, that's odd.

00:07:34.675 --> 00:07:38.750
Didn't you lose a front tooth
back at the hot spring?

00:07:41.155 --> 00:07:42.892
- [snorts]

00:07:42.925 --> 00:07:44.962
- Uh...

00:07:46.231 --> 00:07:47.935
- You must
have been seeing things.

00:07:47.969 --> 00:07:51.309
- Not only did I see it,
but I've still got it.

00:07:51.342 --> 00:07:53.079
- You kept it in your pocket?!

00:07:53.113 --> 00:07:55.116
What kind of creep
does something like that?!

00:07:55.150 --> 00:07:58.590
- But you dropped it, so I
thought I'd return it to you.

00:07:58.624 --> 00:08:00.227
- Have you
gone soft in the head?!

00:08:00.260 --> 00:08:01.329
Get rid of that thing!

00:08:01.362 --> 00:08:03.099
- Now scram!
- Ohh!

00:08:07.207 --> 00:08:12.184
- [humming a tune]

00:08:12.217 --> 00:08:14.455
- Like this, like that,

00:08:14.488 --> 00:08:16.292
and then something like this.

00:08:16.325 --> 00:08:19.899
Then I go like this, I... think.

00:08:19.932 --> 00:08:23.974
I wonder why Genya's
in a bad mood all the time.

00:08:24.007 --> 00:08:27.749
Could it be that's he's
just hungry and that's why?

00:08:27.782 --> 00:08:31.289
Hey, I know! We should
ask him to have breakfast.

00:08:31.322 --> 00:08:33.292
- Mm! Mm!

00:08:33.326 --> 00:08:35.898
- You think
it's a good idea too?

00:08:35.932 --> 00:08:37.769
We already soaked
in the hot spring,

00:08:37.802 --> 00:08:40.173
so I'm sure he'd say yes!

00:08:40.206 --> 00:08:41.743
- [giggles]

00:08:41.777 --> 00:08:44.816
- I like Genya. I'd like
to get closer to him.

00:08:46.853 --> 00:08:49.325
Man, braiding
sure is difficult.

00:08:49.358 --> 00:08:50.459
But look! Now you've got

00:08:50.493 --> 00:08:52.999
the same hairstyle
as Ms. Kanroji!

00:08:53.032 --> 00:08:54.335
- [squeals]

00:08:54.368 --> 00:08:55.938
[laughs]

00:08:56.907 --> 00:08:57.908
- Hey...

00:08:57.942 --> 00:09:02.051
Nezuko, doesn't the moon
look beautiful tonight?

00:09:02.084 --> 00:09:04.121
- [squeals]

00:09:04.155 --> 00:09:05.323
[crickets chirping]

00:09:05.357 --> 00:09:06.425
[sandals clattering]

00:09:06.458 --> 00:09:09.665
- [humming a tune]

00:09:19.986 --> 00:09:22.959
- I might have soaked
a little too long tonight.

00:09:22.992 --> 00:09:25.998
I gotta get to bed
for my early shift tomorrow.

00:09:29.238 --> 00:09:30.541
Hmm?

00:09:30.574 --> 00:09:32.612
A vase? I don't remember

00:09:32.646 --> 00:09:35.149
seeing anything like that
on the way up.

00:09:36.418 --> 00:09:37.789
Who put this here?

00:09:37.822 --> 00:09:40.259
Someone could trip on this
and get hurt.

00:09:41.796 --> 00:09:44.368
- [groaning]
- [bones snapping]

00:09:44.401 --> 00:09:47.608
[tense music]

00:09:50.213 --> 00:09:51.215
[porcelain clatters]

00:09:54.288 --> 00:09:56.826
[porcelain clatters]

00:09:56.860 --> 00:09:58.964
[chorus vocalizing]

00:10:05.812 --> 00:10:08.950
[porcelain scrapes]

00:10:09.919 --> 00:10:12.658
- How horrible. How horrible.

00:10:12.691 --> 00:10:13.860
I suppose I should have known

00:10:13.894 --> 00:10:15.496
that a mountain
swordsmith's flesh

00:10:15.531 --> 00:10:17.835
would be unfit
for my consumption!

00:10:17.868 --> 00:10:21.175
But that's what makes it
so appealing!

00:10:21.208 --> 00:10:25.383
If I can destroy this place,
then those Demon Slayers--

00:10:25.417 --> 00:10:30.694
[laughs] will be without a place
to craft their precious swords!

00:10:30.727 --> 00:10:33.466
- I must try to move quickly.

00:10:33.499 --> 00:10:35.103
I must try to move quickly!

00:10:35.136 --> 00:10:39.478
Thanks to Gyokko, we were able
to locate their hidden village.

00:10:39.512 --> 00:10:40.881
- [tiles grinding]
- [shudders]

00:10:40.914 --> 00:10:44.789
But that doesn't change
the fact that my lord is angry!

00:10:45.591 --> 00:10:47.728
Quickly, quickly.

00:10:47.762 --> 00:10:50.066
<i>We must kill
every one of them.</i>

00:10:50.100 --> 00:10:54.374
<i>Anyone who opposes my lord
must be eliminated.</i>

00:10:55.711 --> 00:10:57.582
<i>[wind blowing]</i>

00:10:57.615 --> 00:10:58.817
<i>[sword slices]</i>

00:11:02.791 --> 00:11:04.662
<i>[wind blowing]</i>

00:11:04.695 --> 00:11:06.064
<i>[sword slices]</i>

00:11:07.802 --> 00:11:09.238
[crickets chirping]

00:11:09.271 --> 00:11:12.377
[footsteps crunching]

00:11:15.483 --> 00:11:16.786
- Eh?

00:11:21.161 --> 00:11:22.798
Old man? You done?

00:11:24.467 --> 00:11:25.938
You're not here.

00:11:37.595 --> 00:11:38.863
Brother.

00:11:41.636 --> 00:11:44.074
I have no choice
but to do this.

00:11:45.544 --> 00:11:48.684
- [soft breathing]

00:11:48.717 --> 00:11:49.920
[gags]

00:11:49.953 --> 00:11:53.627
- Have you seen
the swordsmith named Kanamori?

00:11:53.661 --> 00:11:56.365
- Oh, hey, Tokito!
Is something wrong?!

00:11:56.398 --> 00:11:59.237
- Wait, hold on a second.
Did you just pinch my nose?

00:11:59.270 --> 00:12:00.874
- Yes, I did.

00:12:00.908 --> 00:12:02.945
And you took
far too long to react.

00:12:02.978 --> 00:12:07.053
- No, no, I would have sensed it
if there were any animosity!

00:12:07.087 --> 00:12:10.661
- Yes, but would you pinch
someone's nose with animosity?

00:12:10.694 --> 00:12:13.499
- Sure, I know Mr. Kanamori.

00:12:13.533 --> 00:12:14.669
What's wrong?

00:12:14.702 --> 00:12:17.440
If I had to guess,
he's with Mr. Haganezuka.

00:12:17.474 --> 00:12:21.750
- Kanamori's been appointed
to be my new swordsmith.

00:12:21.783 --> 00:12:23.854
So where's Haganezuka, then?

00:12:23.887 --> 00:12:26.124
- I don't know. Let's go look!

00:12:28.329 --> 00:12:31.503
- Why do you care so much
about other people?

00:12:31.536 --> 00:12:32.604
Isn't there something

00:12:32.638 --> 00:12:34.909
you'd rather do for yourself
right now?

00:12:35.811 --> 00:12:38.049
- Life has a way
of rewarding good deeds.

00:12:38.082 --> 00:12:41.322
Oftentimes when you help others,
you're helping yourself.

00:12:41.355 --> 00:12:44.395
I was planning to go anyway,
so why not?

00:12:44.428 --> 00:12:45.429
- Huh.

00:12:47.201 --> 00:12:47.968
Huh?

00:12:48.001 --> 00:12:50.774
Hold on.
Repeat what you just said.

00:12:50.808 --> 00:12:52.143
Say it. Say it.

00:12:52.177 --> 00:12:55.216
- Huh? That I was
planning to go anyway?

00:12:55.250 --> 00:12:56.218
Ow!

00:12:56.251 --> 00:12:57.120
- [grunting]

00:12:57.154 --> 00:12:59.625
- I'm glad to see
you're awake, Nezuko.

00:12:59.659 --> 00:13:00.861
That hurt.

00:13:01.663 --> 00:13:03.433
[Nezuko grunting]

00:13:03.466 --> 00:13:05.069
- Huh.

00:13:07.474 --> 00:13:10.046
<i>[peaceful music]</i>

00:13:10.079 --> 00:13:12.852
- Let's go see Mr. Haganezuka.

00:13:12.885 --> 00:13:16.091
- [grunting]

00:13:16.125 --> 00:13:19.666
- This girl is certainly
an odd creature, isn't she?

00:13:19.699 --> 00:13:21.803
- What?! What do you mean?!

00:13:21.836 --> 00:13:23.941
- Well, I just get this feeling.

00:13:23.974 --> 00:13:28.082
Let's see. How do I explain?

00:13:28.115 --> 00:13:31.155
I get the feeling
that I've met this girl before.

00:13:31.188 --> 00:13:33.158
Was she like this
when I met her?

00:13:33.192 --> 00:13:35.564
- How should I put it?
- Hmm?

00:13:35.598 --> 00:13:37.066
- [nervous chuckle]

00:13:38.303 --> 00:13:40.206
Hmm.

00:13:41.208 --> 00:13:42.511
[Tokito] Hmm.

00:13:43.847 --> 00:13:45.383
[Nezuko] Hmm.

00:13:46.620 --> 00:13:48.022
- Hmm?

00:13:48.055 --> 00:13:49.859
Is someone else here?

00:13:49.893 --> 00:13:51.495
- It seems like it.

00:13:53.032 --> 00:13:55.469
<i>[ominous music]</i>

00:13:58.242 --> 00:14:00.514
- [shudders]

00:14:00.547 --> 00:14:03.553
[weeping]

00:14:07.493 --> 00:14:08.964
[heart beats]

00:14:08.997 --> 00:14:11.603
- [crying]
<i>- [Tanjiro] Wh--What is that?</i>

00:14:11.636 --> 00:14:13.573
<i>Is it a demon?</i>

00:14:13.606 --> 00:14:16.379
<i>What is a demon doing here?</i>

00:14:16.412 --> 00:14:19.719
<i>I didn't notice him
until I saw him.</i>

00:14:19.753 --> 00:14:21.488
<i>There's no doubt.</i>

00:14:21.522 --> 00:14:23.358
<i>This demon's an Upper Rank!</i>

00:14:25.865 --> 00:14:27.066
<i>[thrilling music]</i>

00:14:27.100 --> 00:14:28.503
- Mist Breathing...

00:14:29.905 --> 00:14:31.074
Fourth Form...

00:14:31.108 --> 00:14:32.410
Shifting Flow Slash.

00:14:32.444 --> 00:14:33.714
[Hantengu whimpers]

00:14:33.747 --> 00:14:34.715
<i>[singers vocalizing]</i>

00:14:34.749 --> 00:14:36.686
[whimpers]

00:14:36.719 --> 00:14:38.022
<i>- He's quick.</i>

00:14:38.056 --> 00:14:40.025
<i>I couldn't take him out.</i>

00:14:40.059 --> 00:14:42.998
- Please stop it!

00:14:43.032 --> 00:14:46.372
Please stop tormenting me.

00:14:46.405 --> 00:14:48.576
It hurts!

00:14:48.610 --> 00:14:50.146
<i>- Don't lose your nerve!</i>

00:14:50.179 --> 00:14:52.150
<i>This demon is a mass murderer!</i>

00:14:52.184 --> 00:14:55.055
<i>Otherwise, he wouldn't have
been able to dodge that attack!</i>

00:14:56.025 --> 00:14:57.661
<i>Hinokami Kagura...</i>

00:14:57.695 --> 00:14:59.598
<i>[thrilling music]</i>

00:15:00.668 --> 00:15:02.036
<i>Sunflower Thrust!</i>

00:15:02.069 --> 00:15:04.274
[bones creaking]

00:15:04.307 --> 00:15:05.978
- [whimpering]

00:15:06.011 --> 00:15:07.615
<i>- Did I get him?</i>

00:15:07.648 --> 00:15:09.619
<i>Why isn't he fighting back?</i>

00:15:09.652 --> 00:15:11.155
<i>Is he not Upper Rank?</i>

00:15:11.188 --> 00:15:12.958
<i>[singers vocalizing]</i>

00:15:12.992 --> 00:15:15.130
- [grunts]

00:15:15.163 --> 00:15:16.599
- [gags]

00:15:16.633 --> 00:15:18.168
[whimpers]

00:15:18.202 --> 00:15:21.208
- Nezuko! Don't transform here!

00:15:21.241 --> 00:15:23.680
Your demon form is advancing!

00:15:25.349 --> 00:15:27.655
- [gasps]

00:15:27.688 --> 00:15:30.493
[squeals]

00:15:30.527 --> 00:15:32.464
I've been decapitated!

00:15:32.497 --> 00:15:34.602
<i>- He decapitated him!</i>

00:15:34.635 --> 00:15:36.338
<i>And so fast! But...</i>

00:15:36.371 --> 00:15:39.177
<i>Upper Ranks don't
always die so easily,</i>

00:15:39.211 --> 00:15:41.281
<i>even if you behead them.</i>

00:15:42.685 --> 00:15:45.022
Tokito, stay focused!

00:15:46.458 --> 00:15:48.563
<i>[chorus vocalizing]</i>

00:15:56.478 --> 00:15:57.681
<i>[ominous music]</i>

00:16:00.486 --> 00:16:02.558
<i>He split in two!</i>

00:16:02.592 --> 00:16:04.027
<i>One of them grew a head,</i>

00:16:04.060 --> 00:16:06.465
<i>while the other
grew out a body!</i>

00:16:06.499 --> 00:16:08.135
I'll take this one!

00:16:08.168 --> 00:16:11.107
<i>If we can
strike them simultaneously!</i>

00:16:18.089 --> 00:16:19.257
[Nezuko grunts]

00:16:19.290 --> 00:16:21.261
- Nezuko!

00:16:21.294 --> 00:16:22.564
Tokito!

00:16:24.100 --> 00:16:25.870
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:16:25.904 --> 00:16:27.306
[Nezuko growls]

00:16:30.915 --> 00:16:32.718
- [laughs]

00:16:32.751 --> 00:16:34.722
Hey, now! This is pretty fun!

00:16:34.755 --> 00:16:37.962
Did you see how far
that pipsqueak went flying?

00:16:37.995 --> 00:16:40.032
Huh? Did you, Sekido?

00:16:40.066 --> 00:16:42.237
- There's nothing fun
about this.

00:16:42.270 --> 00:16:44.909
All I'm feeling
is uncontrollable rage.

00:16:44.942 --> 00:16:48.917
Karaku, I despise
being lumped in with you.

00:16:48.951 --> 00:16:50.086
- [slurps]

00:16:50.119 --> 00:16:51.488
Ah, is that right?

00:16:51.523 --> 00:16:54.027
Well, good thing
we got separated, then!

00:16:54.061 --> 00:16:56.064
<i>- Again?</i>

00:16:56.098 --> 00:16:57.334
<i>Are we going
to have to behead</i>

00:16:57.367 --> 00:16:59.705
<i>two of them at once again?</i>

00:16:59.739 --> 00:17:02.711
- [growls]

00:17:04.983 --> 00:17:07.588
- [groans]

00:17:07.621 --> 00:17:10.393
<i>What is... this?</i>

00:17:10.427 --> 00:17:12.998
- [jingling]
<i>- It must be that staff!</i>

00:17:13.031 --> 00:17:15.036
<i>This is bad.</i>

00:17:15.069 --> 00:17:16.540
<i>I'm about to...</i>

00:17:16.573 --> 00:17:18.342
<i>lose consciousness.</i>

00:17:20.146 --> 00:17:23.787
<i>Someone's on the--
on the roof?</i>

00:17:23.820 --> 00:17:24.923
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:17:24.956 --> 00:17:26.424
<i>Genya.</i>

00:17:27.928 --> 00:17:29.130
[groans]

00:17:30.099 --> 00:17:31.434
[both gag]

00:17:32.237 --> 00:17:34.676
<i>- What is that? A gun?</i>

00:17:34.709 --> 00:17:35.611
<i>If it is, why does it have</i>

00:17:35.644 --> 00:17:38.248
<i>the same scent
as a Nichirin Sword?</i>

00:17:39.885 --> 00:17:42.156
- I must have missed
one of them.

00:17:44.762 --> 00:17:46.599
- [laughs]

00:17:46.632 --> 00:17:49.638
This is even more fun
and entertaining than I thought.

00:17:49.672 --> 00:17:52.744
- I've never been hit with
an attack that felt like that!

00:17:53.880 --> 00:17:55.016
- Genya, wait!

00:17:55.049 --> 00:17:57.353
No matter what you do,
this demon...

00:17:59.057 --> 00:18:00.393
can't be killed!

00:18:00.426 --> 00:18:02.130
It'll only end up multiplying!

00:18:02.163 --> 00:18:04.535
It gets younger and stronger!

00:18:04.569 --> 00:18:06.873
They're counting on us
beheading them!

00:18:06.906 --> 00:18:08.576
- [chuckles]

00:18:08.610 --> 00:18:12.184
<i>- It's like this demon doesn't
care about being decapitated.</i>

00:18:12.217 --> 00:18:14.388
<i>Meaning its vital spot
isn't its head!</i>

00:18:14.421 --> 00:18:17.929
<i>It's splitting into four
and regenerating!</i>

00:18:17.962 --> 00:18:19.464
<i>Is there a pattern?</i>

00:18:19.497 --> 00:18:21.235
<i>Which part heals up first?</i>

00:18:21.268 --> 00:18:24.407
<i>It has to have
some kind of weakness!</i>

00:18:24.441 --> 00:18:25.711
<i>Find it!</i>

00:18:25.744 --> 00:18:27.080
<i>Figure it out!</i>

00:18:27.113 --> 00:18:28.650
<i>What is it?</i>

00:18:29.618 --> 00:18:30.554
[gasps]

00:18:30.587 --> 00:18:32.925
<i>I thought it split up
into four demons.</i>

00:18:32.958 --> 00:18:33.927
[yelps]

00:18:33.960 --> 00:18:34.962
- [gasps]

00:18:34.996 --> 00:18:37.133
- [laughs]

00:18:37.166 --> 00:18:39.137
This makes my heart sing!

00:18:39.171 --> 00:18:42.612
It's been so long
since I was last split off!

00:18:42.645 --> 00:18:44.481
<i>- This demon can fly!</i>

00:18:44.515 --> 00:18:46.853
<i>All four of them
must have different powers!</i>

00:18:46.886 --> 00:18:49.124
Nezuko, forget about me!

00:18:49.158 --> 00:18:50.126
Try and help Genya!

00:18:50.159 --> 00:18:51.428
[gasps]

00:18:51.461 --> 00:18:52.731
- [gags]

00:18:54.602 --> 00:18:56.906
- You're so weak,
it's almost sad, really.

00:18:56.939 --> 00:18:59.143
- [gasping]

00:19:00.012 --> 00:19:02.718
- [screams]
- [Tanjiro] Genya!

00:19:02.752 --> 00:19:04.187
Nezuko, save him!

00:19:04.221 --> 00:19:06.692
You have to try
and save Genya! Hurry!

00:19:06.726 --> 00:19:07.493
- [grunts]

00:19:07.527 --> 00:19:09.297
- You must be pretty confident

00:19:09.331 --> 00:19:11.636
to be worrying about
someone else right now.

00:19:11.669 --> 00:19:12.638
- [gasps]

00:19:12.671 --> 00:19:14.809
- [inhales]

00:19:14.843 --> 00:19:16.712
<i>- Hinokami Kagura!</i>

00:19:18.817 --> 00:19:20.053
- [shrieks]

00:19:20.086 --> 00:19:22.791
- [screams]
- [shriek warbles]

00:19:23.927 --> 00:19:25.496
[laughs]

00:19:25.531 --> 00:19:30.406
Not bad. This is turning out
to be quite the delight!

00:19:31.341 --> 00:19:32.377
[leaves rustling]

00:19:32.410 --> 00:19:34.915
<i>- Grab onto a branch! A branch!</i>

00:19:36.853 --> 00:19:39.725
[groaning]

00:19:39.758 --> 00:19:41.094
[ears ringing]

00:19:41.128 --> 00:19:43.866
[groaning]

00:19:46.338 --> 00:19:48.008
<i>Get up right now!</i>

00:19:48.042 --> 00:19:49.511
<i>Get on your feet!</i>

00:19:49.545 --> 00:19:53.152
<i>The villagers are in danger.
I have to protect them!</i>

00:19:53.185 --> 00:19:55.857
<i>Damn it. My body's gone numb.</i>

00:19:55.890 --> 00:19:57.862
<i>I can't hear anything, either!</i>

00:19:57.895 --> 00:19:59.064
- [groans]
- [ears ringing]

00:19:59.097 --> 00:20:00.066
[gasps]

00:20:00.099 --> 00:20:01.068
<i>[ominous music]</i>

00:20:01.101 --> 00:20:02.170
[gasps]

00:20:02.203 --> 00:20:05.375
- [inhaling]

00:20:09.785 --> 00:20:10.754
<i>[tense music]</i>

00:20:10.787 --> 00:20:11.756
<i>[singers vocalizing]</i>

00:20:11.790 --> 00:20:14.361
<i>- I got blasted
quite a distance.</i>

00:20:14.394 --> 00:20:16.799
<i>I've got to get back quickly.</i>

00:20:19.037 --> 00:20:21.241
- [panting]
- [growling]

00:20:22.243 --> 00:20:23.679
<i>[Tokito]
A demon and a child.</i>

00:20:24.581 --> 00:20:26.886
<i>Unfortunately,
as a swordsmith,</i>

00:20:26.919 --> 00:20:28.623
<i>the child is still unseasoned.</i>

00:20:28.656 --> 00:20:31.529
<i>Therefore saving him
is a low priority.</i>

00:20:31.562 --> 00:20:34.535
<i>Judging by its presence,
that's not the main body,</i>

00:20:34.568 --> 00:20:36.906
<i>but something
generated by a spell.</i>

00:20:36.939 --> 00:20:38.108
- [screams]

00:20:38.142 --> 00:20:40.547
[grunting]

00:20:40.581 --> 00:20:43.352
<i>- There's no reason
to stop and fight it now.</i>

00:20:43.385 --> 00:20:45.524
<i>If the entire village
is under attack,</i>

00:20:45.557 --> 00:20:47.561
<i>then the village chief
comes first.</i>

00:20:47.594 --> 00:20:49.865
<i>Those with
greater skills and talents</i>

00:20:49.898 --> 00:20:51.569
<i>are my top priority to protect.</i>

00:20:51.602 --> 00:20:53.806
- [yelling]
- [growling]

00:20:55.075 --> 00:20:58.316
<i>- My objective is to annihilate
that Upper Rank demon</i>

00:20:58.349 --> 00:21:00.587
<i>and protect the village
at all costs.</i>

00:21:00.621 --> 00:21:01.655
- [snarls]

00:21:01.689 --> 00:21:04.796
<i>- Saving an inexperienced
budding swordsmith</i>

00:21:04.829 --> 00:21:05.663
<i>won't amount to any--</i>

00:21:05.697 --> 00:21:08.369
- Life has a way
of rewarding good deeds.

00:21:08.402 --> 00:21:10.874
Often when you help others,
you're helping yourself

00:21:10.907 --> 00:21:12.878
- [gasps]

00:21:12.911 --> 00:21:14.915
- [groaning]

00:21:17.086 --> 00:21:18.590
- [snarls]

00:21:18.623 --> 00:21:20.894
[gags]

00:21:22.864 --> 00:21:23.867
- [moans]

00:21:23.900 --> 00:21:26.171
<i>[traditional music]</i>

00:21:26.204 --> 00:21:27.541
[gasps]

00:21:27.574 --> 00:21:28.944
- Run.

00:21:28.977 --> 00:21:31.582
- It's you.

00:21:33.953 --> 00:21:35.557
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:21:35.590 --> 00:21:39.430
- Run for it before you
get in my way even more.

00:21:42.905 --> 00:21:44.876
<i>["Koi Kogare" playing]</i>

00:21:44.909 --> 00:21:51.922
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:23:12.951 --> 00:23:14.722
[page rustles]

00:23:14.755 --> 00:23:16.759
- A demon showed up
while Mr. Haganezuka

00:23:16.792 --> 00:23:19.798
was off working on your sword,
but are you all right?

00:23:19.832 --> 00:23:21.401
- Mm. Thankfully,

00:23:21.435 --> 00:23:24.006
Mr. Haganezuka
forged this for me.

00:23:24.040 --> 00:23:27.112
It's good to see
Mr. Haganezuka hasn't changed!

00:23:27.146 --> 00:23:31.254
- If he did, it wouldn't
be for the better! [laughs]

00:23:31.288 --> 00:23:34.060
- Now it's time
for a Taisho-era secret!

00:23:34.094 --> 00:23:37.300
Mr. Haganezuka has wind chimes
on his umbrella,

00:23:37.333 --> 00:23:38.770
because he really likes
wind chimes!

00:23:38.803 --> 00:23:41.576
And when he was little,
every time he threw a tantrum,

00:23:41.609 --> 00:23:43.579
the grownups around him
would play wind chimes

00:23:43.613 --> 00:23:45.283
to try and quiet him down.

00:23:45.316 --> 00:23:46.819
Wow, I didn't know that.

00:23:46.853 --> 00:23:48.388
- This is for you, Mr. Tanjiro.

00:23:48.421 --> 00:23:49.959
- If you think
something like a wind chime

00:23:49.992 --> 00:23:53.700
will put me in a better mood,
you couldn't be more wrong!

00:23:53.733 --> 00:23:55.469
- [roaring]
- [both] Chime, chime, chime!

00:23:55.503 --> 00:23:57.373
- Stop treating me like a child!

00:23:57.406 --> 00:23:58.743
[both] Chime, chime, chime!

00:23:58.776 --> 00:24:02.383
- Up Next, Episode 4,
"Thank You, Tokito."

00:24:02.416 --> 00:24:03.653
Have you calmed down now?

00:24:03.686 --> 00:24:05.356
- I said I'm not a child!

00:24:05.389 --> 00:24:06.892
[both] Chime, chime, chime!

